        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">chronic highly frequent primary myofascial orofacial pain with pain referral</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010232 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010232">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010003"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Myofascial pain caused by an underlying disorder (inflammation, infection or muscle spasm).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
        <terms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-07-01T17:44:16Z</terms:created>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010296"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ICOP number: 2.2</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">secondary myofascial orofacial pain</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010233 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010233">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010232"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002410"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010291"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Pain of tendon origin, affected by jaw movement, function or parafunction and replicated by provocation-testing of the relevant masticatory tendon. Limitation of mandibular movement(s) secondary to pain may be present. The temporalis tendon is a common site of tendonitis and may refer pain to the teeth and other nearby structures. Tendonitis can also occur in other masticatory muscle tendons.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
        <terms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-07-01T17:46:19Z</terms:created>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010296"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ICOP number: 2.2.1</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">myofascial orofacial pain attributed to tendonitis</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010234 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010234">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010232"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002410"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010305"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Pain caused by myositis affecting one or more masticatory muscles, with clinical characteristics of inﬂammation or infection: oedema, erythema and/or increased temperature. It generally arises acutely following direct trauma of the muscle or from infection, or chronically with autoimmune disease. Limitation of unassisted mandibular movements secondary to pain is often present. Calciﬁcation of the muscle can occur (i.e. myositis ossiﬁcans).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
        <terms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-07-01T17:48:14Z</terms:created>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010296"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ICOP number: 2.2.2</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">myofascial orofacial pain attributed to myositis</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010235 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010235">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010232"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Pain caused by sudden, involuntary, reversible tonic contraction of a muscle. Such spasm may affect any of the masticatory muscles. Acute malocclusion may be present.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
        <terms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-07-01T17:49:34Z</terms:created>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010296"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ICOP number: 2.2.3</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">myofascial orofacial pain attributed to muscle spasm</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010236 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010236">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010128"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002410"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010306"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>TMJ pain caused by persistent inflammation of articular tissues (due, for example, to trauma, infection, crystal deposition or autoimmune disorder). TMJ pain is common in TMJ arthritis, but TMJ arthritis can be present without pain.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
        <terms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-07-01T17:52:37Z</terms:created>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010296"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ICOP number: 3.2.1</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temporomandibular joint pain attributed to arthritis</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010237 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010237">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010236"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002410"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010307"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Temporomandibular joint pain due to arthritis with evidence of systemic inflammatory joint disease but not evidence that associates it with the TMJ pain or no evidence of rheumatological disease.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
        <terms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-07-01T17:53:36Z</terms:created>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010296"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ICOP number: 3.2.1.1</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temporomandibular joint pain attributed to non-systemic arthritis</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010238 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010238">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010236"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002410"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010308"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Temporomandibular joint due to arthritis with evidence of systemic inflammatory joint disease, pain developed in close temporal relation to other symptoms, and either the pain has significantly worsened in parallel with worsening of the systemic inflammatory joint disease or the pain has significantly improved or resolved with treatment of the systemic inflammatory joint disease.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
        <terms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2025-07-01T17:54:43Z</terms:created>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010296"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ICOP number: 3.2.1.2</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temporomandibular joint pain attributed to systemic arthritis</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010239 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010239">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OHD_0010128"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>TMJ pain caused by TMJ disc displacement in the absence of TMJ arthritis. TMJ pain can here be due to mechanical derangements within the joint.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:32103673</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731"/>
