        <obo:IAO_0000115>The fibrous investing tissue, covered by keratinized epithelium, that immediately surrounds a tooth and is contiguous with its periodontal ligament and with the mucosal tissues of the mouth[Glossary of Periodontal Terms 2001].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>FMA has a 3-level breakdown of jaws into: region, jaw (skeleton+gums), skeleton.</obo:IAO_0000116>
