        <obo:IAO_0000115>An epithelium that is part of the mouth and lines the oral cavity, typically stratified squamous, and may be para-, ortho- or non- keratinized. Primary barrier between oral environment and deeper tissues.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>consider including separate class for developmental structure (adult human is stratified; in EHDAA2 is unilaminar)</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000001>The epithelium that lines the oral cavity. The oral epithelium epithelial cells with many short microvilli as well as mucous cells, rodlet cells and taste buds[ZFIN:ZDB-PUB-060921-12, ZFIN:ZDB-PUB-091204-24].</obo:UBPROP_0000001>
        <obo:UBPROP_0000011>the avian oral epithelium has the developmental capacity to initiate tooth developmental programs with underlying grafts of non-avian oral ectomesenchyme</obo:UBPROP_0000011>
