        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000061"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms[GO].</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>in some organisms such as drosophila, muscles can be single cells. This class groups together all discrete muscle elements, from multicellular muscle organs in vertebrates, to individual single-cell muscles in drisophila</obo:IAO_0000232>
